cdx6500PPCTALCPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTALCPortTable
cdx6500PPCTALCPortTable.description: This table contains ALC Port configuration parameters

cdx6500PPCTALCPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTALCPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTALCPortEntry.description: Entries in the ALC Port Configuration Table.

alcPCfgSubtype.name: alcPCfgSubtype
alcPCfgSubtype.description: This is the ALC port subtype. alcHpad - Host PAD. alcTpad - Terminal PAD.

alcPCfgPortControl.name: alcPCfgPortControl
alcPCfgPortControl.description: Specify any of the following port control options: simp : Simple connection with no control signal handshake. dtr : Connection with DTR control signal handshake. emri : Port emulates a modem and does dial-in/out handshake with RI. emdc : Port emulates a modem and does dial-in/out handshake with DCD. alcDte : DTE emulation with RTS/CTS handshake.

alcPCfgClockSource.name: alcPCfgClockSource
alcPCfgClockSource.description: int : Internal clock source. ext : External clock source.

alcPCfgClockSpeed.name: alcPCfgClockSpeed
alcPCfgClockSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second, when using internal clocking.

alcPCfgPollDelayTimer.name: alcPCfgPollDelayTimer
alcPCfgPollDelayTimer.description: This is the delay in milliseconds to impose between poll cycles if no interchanges are polled. Valid on TPAD lines only.

alcPCfgHostTimeout.name: alcPCfgHostTimeout
alcPCfgHostTimeout.description: On a poll coerced line, the host is considered to be down if a poll is not received within this time, specified in milliseconds. Valid on HPAD lines only.

alcPCfgMaxMesgSize.name: alcPCfgMaxMesgSize
alcPCfgMaxMesgSize.description: This specifies the maximum size of messages that can be sent or received on this line excluding padding characters. TPAD may receive multiple messages in a frame, HPAD may transmit multiple messages in a frame.

alcPCfgMinIntrvlBetweenPolls.name: alcPCfgMinIntrvlBetweenPolls
alcPCfgMinIntrvlBetweenPolls.description: The minimum length of time, in milliseconds, between polls issued on this line. Valid on TPAD lines only.

alcPCfgRtsCtsTimeout.name: alcPCfgRtsCtsTimeout
alcPCfgRtsCtsTimeout.description: The time in milliseconds, within which CTS must be raised following the RTS signal.

alcPCfgLeadPadChar.name: alcPCfgLeadPadChar
alcPCfgLeadPadChar.description: This is the character to use when inserting leading padding characters.

alcPCfgNumLeadPadChars.name: alcPCfgNumLeadPadChars
alcPCfgNumLeadPadChars.description: This is the number of leading padding characters to use.

alcPCfgTrailPadChar.name: alcPCfgTrailPadChar
alcPCfgTrailPadChar.description: This is the character to use when inserting trailing padding characters.

alcPCfgNumTrailPadChars.name: alcPCfgNumTrailPadChars
alcPCfgNumTrailPadChars.description: This is the number of trailing padding characters to use.

alcPCfgALCLineOptions.name: alcPCfgALCLineOptions
alcPCfgALCLineOptions.description: Select options on this ALC port as follows: NONE : no option specified EMB_SYNC : Sychronization characters are inserted between messages in the same frame. MASK8 : Indicates that the `8' bit is treated as zero when examining interchange addresses on this line. COERCE : Poll coercion is used. CLASH : Poll responses will be aborted if a poll is received whilst a response to a previous poll is being transmitted. RFRTM : Responses will be generated to Response and Forward RTM messages. RZRTM : Responses will be generated to enquiry RTM messages. SOFT_SYNC : Selects software synchronization. NULLS : Nulls are allowed in the data stream. BACKTOBACK : Frames may be received back to back. Any combination of the above maybe specified by summing (e.g. NULLS+BACKTOBACK. . .).

alcPCfgConnType.name: alcPCfgConnType
alcPCfgConnType.description: none : No connection. x25 : Connection type is X.25. nc : Skipped during configuration

alcPCfgAcallMnemonic.name: alcPCfgAcallMnemonic
alcPCfgAcallMnemonic.description: This is the mnemonic to be used to establish the call when the call request is issued. The mnemonic must be defined in the mnemonic table. If no mnemonic is specified, ALP PAD will wait for the call. It consists of 0-8 alphanumeric characters, and the space character is used to blank the field.

alcPCfgCallingAddress.name: alcPCfgCallingAddress
alcPCfgCallingAddress.description: The calling address to be used in outbound calls. It consists of 0-15 BCD digits, and the space character is used to blank the field.

alcPCfgCUD.name: alcPCfgCUD
alcPCfgCUD.description: The Call User Data field to be used in outbound calls. It consists of a list of up to 16 hexadecimal numbers between 0 and FF, separated by commas.

alcPCfgNumOfBuffers.name: alcPCfgNumOfBuffers
alcPCfgNumOfBuffers.description: This defines the number of buffers that are available for data transfer in each direction. Each buffer will hold one message.

alcPCfgInHeader.name: alcPCfgInHeader
alcPCfgInHeader.description: This data is assumed to be at the start of all messages received from X.25. If IA and/or TA are specified in the header, the values associated with these positions are checked against the IA and TA associated with the header is then removed from the message, and replaced by the IA and TA associated with the connection.

alcPCfgOutHeader.name: alcPCfgOutHeader
alcPCfgOutHeader.description: This data is prefixed to all messages sent to X.25. If IA and/or TA are specified in the header, the IA and TA associated with the connection are inserted into the outgoing message at the positions specified by the header. The IA and TA received from ALC are removed and replaced with the OUT Header.

alcPCfgReconnectTimeout.name: alcPCfgReconnectTimeout
alcPCfgReconnectTimeout.description: The time in seconds between attempts to establish an X.25 virtual circuit when the ALP connection is enabled, or after the SVC has been cleared.

alcPCfgInactivityTimeout.name: alcPCfgInactivityTimeout
alcPCfgInactivityTimeout.description: The time in seconds after which the call is cleared if no data is transmitted or received. A value of 0 disables the timer.

alcPCfgDebounceTimeout.name: alcPCfgDebounceTimeout
alcPCfgDebounceTimeout.description: This defines the time in seconds for which the PAD waits before implementing the shutdown action. If the time out is 0, shutdown occurs immediately.

alcPCfgParity.name: alcPCfgParity
alcPCfgParity.description: none : No parity will be used. odd : All messages sent to X.25 will have odd parity. nc : Skipped during configuration

alcPCfgConnOptions.name: alcPCfgConnOptions
alcPCfgConnOptions.description: Options controlling the behaviour of the connection. NONE : No options are specified. HDR : ALP PAD discards all data messages incoming from the network in which the constant parts of the IN Header do not match the header of the message. ALCSD : If this option is specified and the SVC goes down, then the ALC entity is shutdown. CSD : If this option is specified and the ALC entity goes down, then the associated call is cleared. FLOW : If the number of free buffers decreases to 20% of its maximum, then flow control is imposed on the receiver. It is released when the number of free buffers reaches 50% of its maximum. If the option is not set, messages received when there are no buffers available will be discarded. Note that flow control requests from X.25 are always acted upon, regardless of the setting of this option. USE_ADDR : The address in the received message is used when the message is passed to ALC, and address checking is turned off. Any combination of the above maybe specified by summing (e.g. FLOW+USE_ADDR+. . .).

alcPCfgAvailableMesg.name: alcPCfgAvailableMesg
alcPCfgAvailableMesg.description: This specifies the text of a message that is broadcast to the ALC entity associated with this connection after a message from that terminal has been discarded due to the X.25 VC being down. This message is only sent if an Unavailable message has previously been sent to one of the terminals associated with this connection. If no message is defined, none is sent. The space character is used to blank this field. Note that this is only used on TPAD configurations.

alcPCfgUnavailableMesg.name: alcPCfgUnavailableMesg
alcPCfgUnavailableMesg.description: This specifies the text of a message that is sent to a terminal when a message from that terminal is discarded because the X.25 VC is down. If no message is defined, none is sent. The space character is used to blank this field. Note that this is only used on TPAD configurations.

cdx6500PPCTALCInterchangeTable.name: cdx6500PPCTALCInterchangeTable
cdx6500PPCTALCInterchangeTable.description: This table contains ALC Interchange configuration parameters

cdx6500PPCTALCInterchangeEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTALCInterchangeEntry
cdx6500PPCTALCInterchangeEntry.description: Entries in the ALC Interchange Configuration Table.

alcICfgInterchangeAddress.name: alcICfgInterchangeAddress
alcICfgInterchangeAddress.description: The address of the interchange. Addresses 0D,0F,1D,2D,3D and 3F are illegal as they are used as line control characters.

alcICfgOptionOnInvalidCCC.name: alcICfgOptionOnInvalidCCC
alcICfgOptionOnInvalidCCC.description: The action to be taken on receipt of a message with an invalid ccc. discard : Discard the message ignore : Treat the message as correct. reenter : (TPAD only) The configured `re-enter' message is sent to the terminal. resend : (TPAD only) A resend request message is sent to the terminal.

alcICfgGenTerminalAddress.name: alcICfgGenTerminalAddress
alcICfgGenTerminalAddress.description: Specifies the terminal address to which broadcast messages are sent when the GTA option is specified.

alcICfgHostTimeout.name: alcICfgHostTimeout
alcICfgHostTimeout.description: The host is considered to be down if a poll is not received within this period, which is specified in milliseconds.

alcICfgMaxComponentsPerFrame.name: alcICfgMaxComponentsPerFrame
alcICfgMaxComponentsPerFrame.description: Specifies the maximum number of message segments transmitted in one frame (HPAD) or expected in one frame (TPAD).

alcICfgFastPollCycleCount.name: alcICfgFastPollCycleCount
alcICfgFastPollCycleCount.description: The polling rate for an interchange in fast poll. A poll is issued to this interchange once in every n poll cycles on the line.

alcICfgSlowPollCycleCount.name: alcICfgSlowPollCycleCount
alcICfgSlowPollCycleCount.description: The polling rate for an interchange in slow poll. One slow poll IA is polled every n poll cycles on the line.

alcICfgN1Counter.name: alcICfgN1Counter
alcICfgN1Counter.description: The number of polls that can be sent without receiving a response before the interchange enters slow poll.

alcICfgN2Counter.name: alcICfgN2Counter
alcICfgN2Counter.description: The number of good poll responses required before the interchange enters fast poll.

alcICfgT1Timeout.name: alcICfgT1Timeout
alcICfgT1Timeout.description: The time, in milliseconds, within which an interchange must start responding to a poll.

alcICfgT2Timeout.name: alcICfgT2Timeout
alcICfgT2Timeout.description: The time, in milliseconds, within which an interchange must complete its transmission.

alcICfgReenterMessage.name: alcICfgReenterMessage
alcICfgReenterMessage.description: This specifies the text of a message sent to terminals when a message with an incorrect ccc is received and the action on receipt of an invalid ccc is REENTER. Note that some terminals may require control characters at the start of the message.

alcICfgStartMessage.name: alcICfgStartMessage
alcICfgStartMessage.description: This specifies the text of a message sent to terminals when polling of this interchange is started and the STST option is configured. Note that some terminals may require control characters at the start of the message.

alcICfgStopMessage.name: alcICfgStopMessage
alcICfgStopMessage.description: This specifies the text of a message sent to terminals when polling of this interchange is stopped and the STST option is configured. Note that some terminals may require control characters at the start of the message.

alcICfgOptions.name: alcICfgOptions
alcICfgOptions.description: Select options on this ALC Interchange as follows : NONE : no option specified GTA : (TPAD only) Indicates that there is a general terminal address which may be used for broadcasting to all terminals on the interchange. NOPOLL : (TPAD only) Indicates that this interchange is not to be polled. RESET : Indicates that the interchange is capable of handling ALC Reset messages. STST : (TPAD only) Indicates that the configured start and stop messages should be transmitted when polling is started or stopped. Any combination of the above maybe specified by summing (e.g. GTA+NOPOLL+. . .).

alcICfgValidTAList.name: alcICfgValidTAList
alcICfgValidTAList.description: A list of hexadecimal numbers between 1 and 3F separated by commas. /f or /r after each is used to indicate forward or reverse abort respectively. Ranges may be specified by separating two addresses by a dash `-'. Note that the addresses 0D, 1D, 2D, 3D and 3F are illegal. The list of terminal addresses that may be configured on the line, including the forward or reverse abort settings for each terminal.

alcICfgConnType.name: alcICfgConnType
alcICfgConnType.description: none : No connection. x25 : Connection type is X.25. nc : Skipped during configuration

cdx6500PPCTALCTerminalTable.name: cdx6500PPCTALCTerminalTable
cdx6500PPCTALCTerminalTable.description: This table contains ALC Terminal configuration parameters

cdx6500PPSTALCPortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTALCPortTable
cdx6500PPSTALCPortTable.description: This table contains ALC Port Statistics parameters.

cdx6500PPSTALCPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTALCPortEntry
cdx6500PPSTALCPortEntry.description: Entries in the ALC Port Statistics Table.

alcPStatsPortState.name: alcPStatsPortState
alcPStatsPortState.description: Current Port State. connecting:The line has been enabled by the operator, but polling has not yet been established. online :The line is active. offline :The line has been disabled by the operator. pending :The line is inactive because of conditions detected by ALP PAD (X.25 virtual circuit not active). timedOut :The line is not being polled. This will be displayed on poll coerced HPAD lines only. flowCtrl :The application (ALP PAD) has imposed flow control on the line. na :Value not Available

alcPStatsPolls.name: alcPStatsPolls
alcPStatsPolls.description: Number of polls transmitted or received.

alcPStatsGAs.name: alcPStatsGAs
alcPStatsGAs.description: Number of Go Ahead messages transmitted or received.

alcPStatsResets.name: alcPStatsResets
alcPStatsResets.description: Number of Reset messages transmitted or received.

alcPStatsDiscardBadIAIn.name: alcPStatsDiscardBadIAIn
alcPStatsDiscardBadIAIn.description: Number of received messages discarded due to bad Interchange Address.

alcPStatsDiscardBadIAOut.name: alcPStatsDiscardBadIAOut
alcPStatsDiscardBadIAOut.description: Number of transmitted messages discarded due to bad Interchange Address.

alcPStatsCCCErrors.name: alcPStatsCCCErrors
alcPStatsCCCErrors.description: Number of messages received with an invalid checksum.

alcPStatsPortStatus.name: alcPStatsPortStatus
alcPStatsPortStatus.description: Current Port Status. na :Value not Available

alcPStatsConnState.name: alcPStatsConnState
alcPStatsConnState.description: Current state of the connection. online :The connection is available for data transfer. offline :The connection has been disabled by an operator. connecting:The ALP PAD is attempting to make the X.25 virtual circuit available for use. inactive :The inactivity timer has expired, so the virtual circuit has been dropped. Data received from ALC will cause the connection to be re-established. pending :The CSD option has been configured and the ALC entity is currently down; hence the ALP PAD has disabled the virtual circuit. na :Value not Available

alcPStatsALCMesgsIn.name: alcPStatsALCMesgsIn
alcPStatsALCMesgsIn.description: The number of messages received from ALC.

alcPStatsALCMesgsOut.name: alcPStatsALCMesgsOut
alcPStatsALCMesgsOut.description: The number of messages transmitted to ALC.

alcPStatsX25MesgsIn.name: alcPStatsX25MesgsIn
alcPStatsX25MesgsIn.description: The number of messages received from X.25.

alcPStatsX25MesgsOut.name: alcPStatsX25MesgsOut
alcPStatsX25MesgsOut.description: The number of messages transmitted to X.25.

alcPStatsALCCharsIn.name: alcPStatsALCCharsIn
alcPStatsALCCharsIn.description: The number of characters received from ALC.

alcPStatsALCCharsOut.name: alcPStatsALCCharsOut
alcPStatsALCCharsOut.description: The number of characters transmitted to ALC.

alcPStatsX25CharsIn.name: alcPStatsX25CharsIn
alcPStatsX25CharsIn.description: The number of characters received from X.25.

alcPStatsX25CharsOut.name: alcPStatsX25CharsOut
alcPStatsX25CharsOut.description: The number of characters transmitted to X.25.

alcPStatsALCDiscardedMesgsEntityDown.name: alcPStatsALCDiscardedMesgsEntityDown
alcPStatsALCDiscardedMesgsEntityDown.description: The number of messages received by ALC for which the destination entity is unable to process the data.

alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsEntityDown.name: alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsEntityDown
alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsEntityDown.description: The number of messages received by X.25 for which the destination entity is unable to process the data.

alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsBadALCAddr.name: alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsBadALCAddr
alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsBadALCAddr.description: The number of messages received from X.25 for which the addresses specified do not match those associated with the connection.

alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsBadHeader.name: alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsBadHeader
alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsBadHeader.description: The number of messages received by X.25 of which the IN header configured does not match the header present in the message.

alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsTooLong.name: alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsTooLong
alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsTooLong.description: The number of messages received from X.25 that were discarded because they were longer than the allowable ALC maximum configured.

alcPStatsALCDiscardedMesgsQFull.name: alcPStatsALCDiscardedMesgsQFull
alcPStatsALCDiscardedMesgsQFull.description: The number of messages discarded because the ALC outbound message queue was full.

alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsQFull.name: alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsQFull
alcPStatsX25DiscardedMesgsQFull.description: The number of messages discarded because the X.25 outbound message queue was full.

alcPStatsCurrTxALCQSize.name: alcPStatsCurrTxALCQSize
alcPStatsCurrTxALCQSize.description: The number of messages currently queued in the ALC outbound message queue for transmission.

alcPStatsCurrTxX25QSize.name: alcPStatsCurrTxX25QSize
alcPStatsCurrTxX25QSize.description: The number of messages currently queued in the X.25 outbound message queue for transmission.

alcPStatsMaxTxALCQSize.name: alcPStatsMaxTxALCQSize
alcPStatsMaxTxALCQSize.description: The maximum (highwater mark) size of the ALC outbound queue so far.

alcPStatsMaxTxX25QSize.name: alcPStatsMaxTxX25QSize
alcPStatsMaxTxX25QSize.description: The maximum (highwater mark) size of the X.25 outbound queue so far.

cdx6500PPSTALCInterchangeTable.name: cdx6500PPSTALCInterchangeTable
cdx6500PPSTALCInterchangeTable.description: This table contains ALC Interchange Statistics parameters.

cdx6500PPSTALCInterchangeEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTALCInterchangeEntry
cdx6500PPSTALCInterchangeEntry.description: Entries in the ALC Interchange Statistics Table.

alcIStatsInterchangeAddress.name: alcIStatsInterchangeAddress
alcIStatsInterchangeAddress.description: The address of the interchange. Addresses 0D,0F,1D,2D,3D and 3F are illegal as they are used as line control characters.

alcIStatsInterchangeState.name: alcIStatsInterchangeState
alcIStatsInterchangeState.description: Current State of this Interchange. online :The interchange is active. This is displayed for HPAD interchanges, and TPAD interchanges configured as NOPOLL, only. offline :The interchange has been disabled by the operator. pending :The interchange is inactive because of conditions detected by the application (ALP PAD). failed :The line with which this interchange is associated is down. timedOut:The interchange is not being polled. This is displayed for HPAD interchanges on non poll-coerced lines only. flowCtrl:The application (ALP PAD) has imposed flow control on the interchange. stopped :The line with which this interchange is associated is in the FLOW CONTROL state. This is valid for TPAD interchanges only. slowPoll:The interchange is in slow poll. fastPoll:The interchange is in fast poll. na :Value not Available
